docs.abstract: Alibaba Group, Chinese Internet retailer set for American initial public offering in September, has made half-dozen major investments in American start-ups over past year; flurry of activity, focused on mobile and e-commerce, is not only aimed at widening company's portfolio but at building connections and trust among venture capitalists ahead of IPO.
